(337, 1, '2018-12-09 22:02:57', '2018-12-10 03:02:57', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And this is where I rant about how hard this project <del>was</del>&nbsp;is! Believe me when I say this...&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://render.bitstrips.com/v2/cpanel/ef2ea898-c606-49aa-baeb-f882a9f55e21-b5c24c80-49cc-4620-be8a-eaffff75f595-v1.png?transparent=1&amp;palette=1\" alt=\"\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using underscores as my starter theme may have been a bit more challenging than I first considered. I thought, are themes really all that difficult to do? Because with underscores (or is it _s?) you really are just getting a blank slate. No fanciness included. Just you  and Wordpress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://dab1nmslvvntp.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/1406217327s-default.png\" alt=\"Default Underscores Style\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is literally what my website looked like when I started. (well not literally because I forgot to take a screenshot before I styled it so I found this on sitepoint, thanks sitepoint) So yeah, I spent most of my time with style.css open and frantically trying to find classes to hook onto so I could add some life to my site. I learned a ton of things, like how much better Gutenberg is compared to the old WP editor. I also got real familiar with the page hierarchy and I feel like I can navigate through all these php files a little better than when I started. I still have a long way to go before I would consider myself any kind of authority but that\'s why we have the \"Show Current Template\" plugin for!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the end of the day I have started something here and I plan to keep refining it and correcting the inevitable mistakes that I have, and will probably continue to make. Kudos underscores team (or however you want to be called) you forced me to stop reverting to WP Ocean and Elementor :D</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->', 'My only Entry', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '325-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-09 22:02:57', '2018-12-10 03:02:57', '', 325, 'http://localhost:8888/325-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
